On Wed, 21 Jan 2004 Claralw(-at-)aol.com wrote:
>I haven't scoped out under a late bay tank, but what I have seen it that
>the tank has a threaded protrusion at the outlet.   a fuel sock goes in
>there, then a spout, a gasket, secured with a aluminium threaded nut
>type thing with a hole for the out spout to stick through.

I can confirm that a '74 standard Bug has this arrangement.  The outlet
spout is about 4" long overall, with a 90 degree bend in it outside the
tank.  The nut has a big hole in the center so you can slide it around
the 90 degree bend after it is loosened.

Matt Roberds
